 soul." And that day when I gently smacked his hand — une toute petite tape — for being rude to your mother — the expression of his eyes — it made me want to cry — and his voice when he said: "I am grateful to you, Zelle. It shall never happen again...."'

She went on in this fashion for quite a long time, making me dismally uncomfortable. I managed at last, after several fruitless attempts, to turn the conversation — I was quite hoarse by that time as she had mislaid her ear-trumpet